{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"04314ac8-738e-4a30-a048-59d183cd8645","content":"Neither — use **`dotnet watch`**.\n\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-runs tests automatically when you save a file.\n- **`dotnet watch run`** — for apps (not test projects).\n\nSince your project is a test project, use:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test\n```\n\n`dotnet test` and `dotnet run` execute once and exit — they don't monitor for file changes. `dotnet watch` is the CLI that provides the hot-reload / live-reload loop.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"25cda8d4-a2c4-4fd8-8b0b-826a917bccb3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to use hot reload with .NET testing. Let me look at the project files to understand what they're working with.","outputTokens":165,"requestId":"7698:3EF0C4:C16A56:E0B5ED:69F2B2A6"},"id":"0789c874-75e0-46be-a3b4-da35eb0a9344","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:38:51.981Z","parentId":"ece2872f-874c-49f5-ad1b-61699846e79f"}
